pg?quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/torque-on-9_2701_bk-wh_P5-5ce4ef3.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1666%2C1111 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/torque-on-9_2701_bk-wh_P5-5ce4ef3.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=2221%2C1481 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/torque-on-9_2701_bk-wh_P5-5ce4ef3.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Canyon Torque:ON 9 2021\" title=\"Canyon Torque:ON 9 2021\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/torque-on-9_2701_bk-wh_P5-5ce4ef3.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\"></picture></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The Torque:ON 9 is the more expensive of two builds at £5,799 and gets Fox Factory suspension and SRAM GX Eagle.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Canyon</i></span></p></div><p>Every Torque:ON rolls on the same DT Swiss H1900 wheelset that’s shod with Maxxis Minion DHF/DHR tyres and is finished with Canyon’s own brand parts, including its Iridium <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-dropper-posts/\">dropper seatpost</a>.</p><p>The Torque:ON 9 retails for £5,799 and has the same chassis and finishing kit, but sees an upgrade to Fox 38 Factory/X2 Factory suspension and <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/groupsets/groupset-mountain/sram-gx-eagle-12-speed-drivetrain-review/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SRAM’s GX Eagle</a> 12-speed transmission with SRAM Code discs.</p><p>Both builds are available with an extra 504Wh battery pack, for an additional £500.</p></section></div>","author":"Oli Woodman","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"5f5b862b390a05cd9b12efa9424991d6ec555d16e6d6166625f3e9062d792352","category":"Cycling"}